parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic door locking mechanism can cause the doors to lock unexpectedly, making it difficult or impossible to exit the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The doors lock automatically when closed
the doors lock when the door handle is used to open the door from the inside
the doors lock when the driver's door is opened
the doors lock while the door latch is opened
the doors lock when exiting the vehicle
the passenger door locks while the door latch is opened or when exiting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty door lock springs can cause the doors to lock unexpectedly, making it difficult or impossible to exit the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The door lock springs break
preventing doors from being unlocked electronically or manually
the door handle fails to open and unlock without maneuvering the door handle and lock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sun visor failure can cause the visor to fall down, obstructing the driver's vision and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The sun visor falls down while driving
the sun visor does not stay up
the sun visor hinge made of plastic wears out
causing the sun visor to fall down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock/latch can cause the door to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to exit the vehicle, which can lead to safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The door locks or unlocks unexpectedly
the door is difficult to open or close
the door locks itself
the door cannot be opened from the inside or outside
the door requires manual holding of the lock/unlock button to open
the door latch assembly breaks or fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the frontal passive restraint belts can lead to a lack of protection for the driver and passenger in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The belts fail to operate
will not go around the tracks
or come apart at the "flap" where the belts snap into the receptacle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can cause the belt to stick or not move, making it difficult or impossible to use the seat belt, which can lead to a lack of protection in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The driver's side motorbelt sticks
the motorized driver seat belt won't move
or the seat belt is worn out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the belt to not retract or retract too tightly, making it difficult or uncomfortable to use the seat belt, which can lead to a lack of protection in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The driver's side shoulder seat belt will not retract
the seat belt retracts too tightly
or the seat belt retractor is too tight.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the belt to not latch or unlatch when touched, making it difficult or impossible to use the seat belt, which can lead to a lack of protection in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The driver's side seat belt buckle failure
unable to latch seat belt
or the seat belt buckle may not engage or may unlatch when touched.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belt can cause the belt to not lock into the anchorage or not fasten, making it difficult or impossible to use the seat belt, which can lead to a lack of protection in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The rear passenger seat belts will not lock into the anchorage
or the rear seat belt buckles fail to fasten.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the CV joint or axle can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or damage to other components.
symptoms: CV boots need constant replacement
axle comes off the wheel
front right drive line spins aimlessly
damage to transfer case components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission malfunctions
failure to downshift
failure to engage into gear
transmission failure to go into reverse from park
transmission failure to disengage from park into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission overheating can cause failure of the transmission, leading to loss of vehicle control or accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle caught on fire at the rear axle
overheating failure of the viscous coupler in the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wheel bearing failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, or damage to other components.
symptoms: Wheel bearing failed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Shifter or transmission control issues can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Cannot get out of park without using release button
transmission does not go from park to drive
and in any gear
it will not go into reverse.
